16
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:35,433
in whose name these two great
and noble men died.

17
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:38,599
We pray for those in England

18
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:42,400
who must continue
to live under tyranny

19
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:46,950
and in fear for their lives
and for their souls.

20
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:51,836
We pray the king ceases to listen
to evil counsel

21
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:56,010
and returns to obedience
and the true faith

22
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:58,039
before it is too late.

23
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:59,639
Attack the pope.

24
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:02,712
We pray to Mary, Mother of God,

25
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:06,879
that England may be redeemed
from heresy

26
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:09,580
and all its evil ways

27
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:12,479
and from the clutches
of the heretics

28
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:15,153
who even now are leading her

29
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:19,114
towards destruction
and damnation.

30
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:23,340
[CHEERlNG]

31
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:37,060
[CROMWELL CLEARS THROAT]

32
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:43,599
George Boleyn, Lord Rochford,
is to marry Lord Morley's daughter.

33
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,399
Yes, Your Majesty.

34
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,639
Lord Morley came to see me.

35
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:52,599
He cannot meet Sir Thomas Boleyn's
demand for a dowry of $300.

36
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:55,479
I assured him that I would make up
the shortfall.

37
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,180
Your Majesty is most generous.

38
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:01,959
How is your survey of the
religious houses progressing?

39
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:04,519
Majesty, the commissioners
are currently examining

40
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,479
houses in the West Country.

41
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:12,840
There and elsewhere,
they tell me they have
uncovered many enormities.

42
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,020
What enormities?

43
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:20,639
They have found the monks
in many places so depraved,

44
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:24,079
so licentious and so corrupt,
that your commissioners

45
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:27,950
already despair
of any perfect reformation.

46
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:32,279
For example, the case of the
celebrated Holy Blood of Hailes.

47
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,199
Supposedly the blood of a saint,

48
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:37,559
used for healing the pilgrims who
flock there hoping for a miracle,

49
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:44,200
it turns out to be the blood of a duck,
which the monks renew regularly.

50
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:48,340
Duck's blood.

51
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:56,719
Well, Mr. Cromwell, what do you
propose we do about it?

52
00:04:56,720 --> 00:05:00,119
If Your Majesty will forgive me,
I think we should be looking for ways

53
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:02,879
to promote Your Majesty's
new monarchy.

54
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,599
What do you have in mind?

55
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,399
One way would be through
the production of plays.

56
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:10,319
Why plays?
Plays are an ideal way

57
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:14,719
of setting forth the abomination and
wickedness of the bishop of Rome.

58
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:17,559
They also are means to demonstrate
to people the obedience

59
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:21,439
that as subjects they owe,
by God's and man's laws,

60
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,279
to Your Majesty.

61
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,919
Good.

62
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:27,319
Then I leave it to you,
Mr. Secretary,

63
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:30,470
to finance and produce
some plays.

64
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:35,430
We must do all we can
to advance our revolution.

65
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:39,660
[SlGHS]

66
