153
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:59,719
CHAMBERLAlN:
Majesty, Sir Henry Norris.

154
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,999
HENRY:
Sir Henry.

155
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,410
Your Majesty.
What can I do for you?

156
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:09,559
Well, as Your Majesty may know,
I recently became a widower.

157
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:12,879
And so naturally,
I'm looking to wed again.

158
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:17,479
And my choice has fallen upon
one of Her Majesty's ladies.

159
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,479
Who?

160
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,980
Lady Margaret Sheldon.

161
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,439
You mean Madge.

162
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,359
Yes.

163
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:31,159
Yes, I believe some people call her
that if they are familiar with her.

164
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:34,359
Have you made your intentions plain
to Miss Sheldon, Sir Henry?

165
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:39,279
No, Your Majesty. I have merely
admired her from a distance.

166
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,479
But I would now
like to take things further,

167
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:45,450
if Your Majesty can think
of no impediment.

168
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:49,473
No. None. You have my permission.

169
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,359
I've known you a long time.

170
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:55,879
I could not think of a more honest,
nor more honourable man.

171
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:59,320
I am deeply grateful
to Your Majesty.

172
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,940
Sir Henry.
Your Majesty.

173
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:14,110
CHAMBERLAlN: His Excellency
the French ambassador.

174
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:20,039
Excellency.
Your Majesty wanted to see me?

175
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:23,559
I wanted to ask after my brother,
the king.

176
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:25,359
His Majesty is very well.

177
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:28,519
Except for his hatred
of the emperor,

178
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:30,039
which is like a disease.

179
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:31,999
So he still wants our friendship?

180
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:36,159
Mon Dieu, he loves you above all
the princes in the world.

181
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:38,660
[###]

182
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:41,510
Then make to him this proposal.

183
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:43,399
That his son Charles,

184
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,039
Duke of Angoulême,
should be betrothed

185
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:49,220
to our beloved daughter,
Elizabeth.

186
