Excuse me, Father.

204
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,500
[###]

205
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:40,260
[MOANlNG]

206
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:38,060
You're very pretty.

207
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,740
Pretty Jane.

208
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,700
Pretty, pretty.

209
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,999
No.

210
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,439
No.

211
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:13,599
No, please.

212
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,279
No, please.

213
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,780
Please, no.

214
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:22,199
No.

215
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,700
No. Aah!

216
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,050
[GEORGE GRUNTlNG]
[JANE SHRlEKlNG]

217
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:45,700
[SOBBlNG]

218
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,700
[CHATTERlNG]

219
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,740
[CROWD CHEERlNG]

220
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:37,199
POPE:
Let us go about our other matters.

221
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:42,433
Now, as much as King John does
Holy Church so handle,

222
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:45,119
so here I curse him

223
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:49,557
with cross, book, bell and candle.

224
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:51,639
[lMlTATES FARTlNG NOlSE]

225
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:54,140
[LAUGHlNG]

226
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:59,115
I will ask God to put him
from his eternal light.

227
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:01,910
I will take him from Christ.

228
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,515
And after the sound of this bell...

229
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:10,155
The bell, you buggers. The bell.

230
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:11,559
[BELL CLANGlNG]

231
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:14,760
And after the sound of this bell...

232
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:20,956
I said, after the sound of this bell,

233
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:27,030
both body and soul,
I will give him to the devil in hell.

234
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,279
[lMlTATES FARTlNG NOlSE]

235
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:32,780
[LAUGHlNG]

236
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,479
And meanwhile--

237
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:37,399
This is a fine piece of work,
Mr. Secretary.

238
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,839
And educative.

239
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:42,340
I wonder who wrote it.

240
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:44,759
Mr. Bale.

241
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:48,879
He was once a priest of the old faith,
but seeing how things went on,

242
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:51,980
became a most passionate
reformer.

243
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:55,719
You know, I think our family
never did anything better

244
00:19:55,720 --> 00:20:01,020
than facilitate and encourage
your own rise, Mr. Secretary.

245
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:04,439
I trust you never forget
that we did so.

246
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:07,190
And all the abbots and bishops

247
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:12,553
will make lots and lots of money.

248
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:15,260
[BOOlNG]

249
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:20,159
I love the pope
as much as ever may be.

250
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:22,839
I prithee heartily,
tell me why you do so?

251
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:26,679
Because I perceive well
the pope is a jolly fellow.

252
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:32,198
A trim fellow. A rich fellow.
Yes, and a merry fellow.

253
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:38,430
He's rich in his royalty
and angelic in his behold.

254
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,620
[CROWD CHEERlNG]

255
